try set fhandle to open for access tmpfile with write permission write (the clipboard as «class PNGf») to fhandle close access fhandle tmpfile on error errMsg number n if n = -1700 then -- Not a PNG clibpoard display dialog "The clibpoard is not a PNG image." buttons {"OK"} end if try close access tmpfile end try
"" end try end alfred_script

set -e
query=$1 filename="$(md5 -q "$query").png" url="https://${IMAGE_UPLOAD_HOSTNAME}/${filename}" chmod 540 "$query" scp "$query" "${IMAGE_UPLOAD_SSH_USER}@${IMAGE_UPLOAD_SSH_HOSTNAME}:${IMAGE_UPLOAD_WEBROOT_PATH}/${filename}"
echo $url

set -e
app_dir="$focusedapp"
cd $SCRIPTS_DIR
if [ -d $app_dir ]; then cat $app_dir/launcher.json fi

require 'json' require 'shellwords' require 'securerandom' require 'tmpdir'
query = ARGV[0] keywords = JSON.parse(File.read(File.join(ENV['SCRIPTS_DIR'], 'meta_launcher.json')), symbolize_names: true).transform_keys(&:to_s) cache_filename = File.join(Dir.tmpdir, "com.temochka.alfred.process-#{ENV.fetch('PROCESS_RUN_ID', SecureRandom.uuid)}")
if query.nil? || query.empty? puts JSON.pretty_generate(items: keywords.values) exit 0 end
matching_keywords = keywords.select do |keyword, item| has_filter = item.dig(:variables, :alfred_filter_script) || item.dig(:variables, :filter_script) query == keyword || keyword.start_with?(query) || query.start_with?(keyword) && has_filter end
match = matching_keywords.values.first if matching_keywords.size == 1 && query.start_with?(matching_keywords.keys.first) filter_query = match && query.gsub(/^#{Regexp.quote(matching_keywords.keys.first)}/, '')
if match && match.dig(:variables, :alfred_filter_script) output = if File.exists?(cache_filename) File.read(cache_filename) else `osascript #{File.join(ENV['SCRIPTS_DIR'], match.dig(:variables, :alfred_filter_script)).shellescape}`.tap do |output| File.open(cache_filename, 'w') { |f| f << output } end end
parsed_output = JSON.parse(output, symbolize_names: true) matching_items = parsed_output.fetch(:items).select { |i| (i[:match] ? i[:match] : i[:title]) =~ /\b#{Regexp.quote(filter_query)}/i } puts JSON.pretty_generate(items: matching_items, variables: match[:variables]) elsif match && match.dig(:variables, :filter_script) parsed_output = JSON.parse(`osascript #{File.join(ENV['SCRIPTS_DIR'], match.dig(:variables, :filter_script)).shellescape} #{filter_query.shellescape}`) puts JSON.pretty_generate(parsed_output.merge(variables: match[:variables])) else puts JSON.pretty_generate(items: matching_keywords.values) end

-- process-looper-script on run tell application "Music" set startPosition to (system attribute "offset1") set endPosition to (system attribute "offset2") set player position to startPosition repeat if player position > endPosition then set player position to startPosition end if delay 0.1 end repeat end tell end run
on run argv tell application "Music" to stop end run

A collection of various productivity shorctus created by Artem Chistyakov (https://temochka.com).
CHANGELOG
- 4.2.0 - Added pb keyword to manipulate clipboard contents. - 4.1.0 - Added IGNORE_CALENDARS config variable to control the same value in ical-alfred. - 4.0.0 - Faster, more interactive launcher. Added a hotkey to launch Process keywords. - 3.4.0 - Add Jekyll search. - 3.3.0 - Add "copy repository URL" for the GitHub workflow. - 3.2.0 - Added a trigger for the script launcher. - 3.1.0 - Added an open file action with a corresponding trigger. - 3.0.0 - Changed keyword to proc. Added optional snippet trigger. - 2.0.0 - Removed app-specific automations (Notes, Calendar, etc.). Can still be run as individual scripts via the improved launcher. - 1.4.0 - Added a "Move Note(s)" shortcut. - 1.3.0 - Added a custom AppleScript launcher. - 1.2.1 - Added documentation for the image sharing workflow. - 1.2.0 - Added an image sharing workflow that works with my personal image sharing hosting. - 1.1.0 - Updated icons, improved calendar script, added README.
